*File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md`\n\n### Purpose\n> \"Provide the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK, including session management with connection pooling, control plane client for Workload Manager interactions, and data plane client for Code Interpreter Router operations.\"\n\n### In Scope\n- `create_session()` utility: `requests.Session` factory with `HTTPAdapter`\n- `ControlPlaneClient`: HTTP client for Workload Manager control plane\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: HTTP client for Code Interpreter data plane via Router\n- Timeout defaults: read `120s`, connect `5.0s`\n- Exception hierarchy: `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n- Utility functions: `read_token_from_file`, `get_logger`\n\n### Out of Scope (verbatim)\n```\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` high-level lifecycle (AR-027)\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` / `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (AR-028)\n- CLI tooling, deployment, sandbox orchestration\n- E2E test infrastructure\n```\n\n### Alternatives Considered (verbatim table)\n| Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|-------------|------|------|----------|\n| **`httpx` (async HTTP)** | Async support, modern API, HTTP/2 | SDK currently sync-only; adds complexity for no immediate benefit | Rejected |\n| **Single unified HTTP client** | Simpler surface area | Control plane and data plane have different auth, URL resolution, and header requirements | Rejected |\n| **Dedicated `Configuration` dataclass** | Centralized config | Current design resolves config at component level; adding a config class would be a breaking refactor | Rejected |\n| **Retry logic in SDK** | Resilience to transient failures | Router and Workload Manager should handle retries; SDK should fail fast to surface issues | **Deferred -- can add later if needed** |\n\n### The one explicitly DEFERRED item (verbatim, from line 89):\n```\n| **Retry logic in SDK** | Resilience to transient failures | Router and Workload Manager should handle retries; SDK should fail fast to surface issues | Deferred -- can add later if needed |\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Design Document (`design.md` -- workspace root)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md`\n\nThis is a comprehensive 792-line design document covering:\n- Architecture with 4-layer diagram\n- Package structure for `sdk-python/`\n- Data structures (exception hierarchy, all client instance state tables)\n- API contracts for all 5 components (HTTP utilities, ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n- Configuration summary table\n- Error handling matrix and timeout strategy\n- Testing strategy with specific test names\n- Usage examples\n\nKey design notes:\n- **No single `Configuration` class** -- defaults and environment resolution are distributed across client constructors\n- **Context manager support** on all clients\n- **Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`** header convention\n- **Timeout safety**: `+2.0s` buffer for command execution read timeout\n- **Connection pooling**: `HTTPAdapter` with configurable pool size\n\n---\n\n## 4. Delta Spec (`delta-spec.md` -- workspace root)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md`\n\nA 366-line Given/When/Then specification covering:\n- HTTP Session Factory (create_session)\n- ControlPlaneClient (constructor, create_session, delete_session, close)\n- CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (constructor, _request, execute_command, run_code, write_file, upload_file, download_file, list_files, close)\n- AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (constructor, bootstrap_session_id, invoke, close)\n- Connection Pool Reuse\n- Utility Functions (read_token_from_file, get_logger)\n- Exception Hierarchy\n\n---\n\n## 5. Tasks 